TYPES OF ARRAY¶

In [4]:
a=np.array(15)  #zero dimensional array
In [5]:
print(a)
print(a.ndim)

15
0
In [8]:
b=np.array([10,20,30])    #one dimensional array
print(b)
print(b.ndim)

[10 20 30]
1
In [9]:
c=np.array([[10,20,30],[40,50,60]])  #two dimensional aray
print(c)
print(c.ndim)
print(c.shape)

[[10 20 30]
 [40 50 60]]
2
(2, 3)
In [10]:
d=np.array([[[10,20,30,40],[10,20,30,40]],[[10,20,30,40],[10,20,30,40]]])   #three dimensional array
print(d)
print(d.ndim)
print(d.shape)

[[[10 20 30 40]
  [10 20 30 40]]

 [[10 20 30 40]
  [10 20 30 40]]]
3
(2, 2, 4)
In [11]:
a=np.array(10,ndmin=2)  #higher dimensional array
print(a)
print(a.ndim)

[[10]]
2

  [ 4  6]]

  [12 14]]]

Out[19]:

COPY() VS VIEW()¶

In [27]:
a=np.array([10,20,30,40,50])
print(a)
b=a.copy()
print(b)
a[1]=15
print(a)
print(b)

[10 20 30 40 50]
[10 20 30 40 50]
[10 15 30 40 50]
[10 20 30 40 50]
In [28]:
a=np.array([10,20,30,40,50])
print(a)
b=a.view()
print(b)
a[1]=15
print(a)
print(b)

[10 20 30 40 50]
[10 20 30 40 50]
[10 15 30 40 50]
[10 15 30 40 50]

In [37]:

  [70 80]]]

NUMBER SORTING¶

In [40]:
a=np.array([99,100,94,95,93,92,91,97,96,98,90])

print(np.sort(a))         #sort 
print(np.sort(a)[::-1])  #reverse sort

[ 99 100  94  95  93  92  91  97  96  98  90]
[ 90  91  92  93  94  95  96  97  98  99 100]
[100  99  98  97  96  95  94  93  92  91  90]
